main event: Two round, bluish-green objects, the size of aircraft, were observed in Turlock, California on January 7, 1956.
interesting points: The objects exhibited erratic movement, going 'up and down' and 'down and up'., Fighters were dispatched to the area but they reported seeing only exceptionally bright stars., The sighting resulted in conflicting opinions, ranging from possible balloons to astronomical phenomena., The exact length of the observation time remains unknown., The report indicates the sightings were consistent with the opinion of the lighting officer regarding the visibility of bright stars.
